### Enforcement

- **Code Reviews:** Pull Requests containing non-English identifiers or filenames **will not be approved**. You will be required to refactor them before the code can be merged.
- **Automation:** Automated linters and pre-commit hooks may be configured to flag non-ASCII characters in identifiers, enforcing this rule automatically.

**The Golden Rule:** If another developer from a different country needs to understand your code without a translator, you have succeeded.

